About Units RSET, DMXGIZMA and TVGIZMA
======================================

    Unit RSET
    ---------
    Data types and untyped constants.  No objects, procedures, functions,
    or typed-constants are included.

	type  TCharArray
	type  TREALNUM
	FirstCmdNum and FirstRegNum constants
        stXXXX constants
        kbXXXX constants
	day and month name constants


    Unit DMXGIZMA
    -------------
    Defines DMX-specific constants, types and functions.

	type  tDMXfieldrec
	accXXXX constants
	cmXXXX constants
	fldXXXX constants

	proc  DisposeSItems	func  DmxStrLen
	func  InitAppendFields	func  InitBlobField
	func  InitEnumField	func  InitTSItemFields
	func  MaxItemStrLen	func  ReadSItems
	func  SItemsLen		proc  WriteSItems


    Unit TVGIZMA
    ------------
    Objects and functions for general Turbo Vision support.

	object TAppA (TApplication)
	object TLtdFrame (TFrame)
	object TLtdWindow (TWindow)
	object TTimeView (TView)
	object TUserScreen (TScroller)

	proc  AssignWinRect	func  DParam
	func  InsertText	func  NewVarItem
	func  SParam		proc  TrimDialog
	func  wnNextAvail


TYPES
-----

    PBoolean	= ^Boolean;
    PByte	= ^Byte;
    PShortInt	= ^ShortInt;
    PInteger	= ^Integer;
    PWord	= ^Word;
    PLongInt	= ^LongInt;
    PReal	= ^Real;

	These types define pointers to their respective types.
	PChar and PString are defined by Turbo Vision in unit OBJECTS.
	Also refer also to TYPE TREALNUM.
	(Unit RSET)


    TCharArray	=  array [0..32767] of char;

	A CHAR array for general use and typecasts.  This is used internally
	by tvDMX and is similar in concept to Turbo Vision's TByteArray.
	TYPE PCharArray is also defined as a pointer to TCharArray.
	(Unit RSET)


    tDMXfieldrec =  RECORD

	This type is used in the chain that describes each field in the
	record.  This chain is initialized by TDmxScroller.InitStruct().

	tDMXfieldrec fields:

	    Next,Prev	:  pDMXfieldrec;
		Pointers to next or previous links in the chain.

	    access	:  byte;
		Read-only, hidden, skip.  (See accXXXX constants.)

	    fieldnum	:  word;
		Number of this field (0=no number).

	    screentab	:  integer;
		Virtual column number to this field.

	    columnwid	:  integer;
		Virtual column number to this field.

	    shownwid	:  integer;
		Virtual column number to this field.

	    typecode	:  char;
		'i', 'W', 'H', 's', 'r', etc.

	    fillvalue	:  char;
		#0 or ' '.

	    upperlimit	:  byte;
		Field's maximum value (set with ^U template code).

	    showzeroes	:  boolean;
		Display zero values (set with ^Z template code).

	    truelen	:  byte;
		Unformatted text length.

	    parenthesis	:  boolean;
		'('/')' characters.

	    decimals	:  byte;
		Number of trailing digits.

	    fieldsize	:  integer;
		Size of field's data TYPE.

	    datatab	:  integer;
		Position in record.

	    template	:  pstring;
		Field template string.


	TYPE pDMXfieldrec is also defined as a pointer to tDMXfieldrec.
	(Unit DMXGIZMA)


    TREALNUM	=  REAL;

	The tvDMX 'R' code accesses data of type TREALNUM.
	Using TREALNUM for floating point numbers makes it easy to
	change defaults from REAL to DOUBLE or other real number type.
	TYPE PREALNUM is also defined as a pointer to TREALNUM.
	(Unit RSET)


CONSTANTS
---------

    accXXXX	=

	These constants define the bits for individual fields.

	    accNormal    =    0;  --regular field
	    accReadOnly  =    1;  --read-only field
	    accHidden    =    2;  --hidden field
	    accSkip      =    4;  --skip field
	    accDelimiter =    8;  --field delimiter (not a field)
	    accSpecA	 =  $20;  --programmer definable
	    accSpecB	 =  $40;  --programmer definable
	    accSpecC	 =  $80;  --programmer definable

	This is used for tDMXfieldrec.access.
	(Unit DMXGIZMA)


    cDMX	= #6#7#4#4#1#2;

	Palette for tvDMX views:
	    1 normal fields
	    2 normal selected field
	    3 read-only field (while selected)
	    4 locked field (while selected)
	    5 delimiter
	    6 border

	This is overridden in unit StdDMX by object TDmxEditDlg to make
	it more suitable for dialog boxes.
	(Unit DMXGIZMA)


    cmDMX		= FirstCmdNum;

	Command constant reserved for future use.  All tvDMX commands
	constants are based on this number.  (See also FirstCmdNum below.)
	(Unit DMXGIZMA)


    cmXXXX		=

	Most command constants are defined in unit DMXGIZMA.PAS, and are
	documented in file COMMANDS.DOC.

	    cmBeep			cmChime
	    cmToggleSound		cmToggleVideo
	    cmUserScreen		FirstCmdNum

	    cmDMX			cmDMX_Ack
	    cmDMX_Bottom		cmDMX_DoubleClick
	    cmDMX_Down			cmDMX_Draw
	    cmDMX_DrawData		cmDMX_End
	    cmDMX_Enter			cmDMX_FieldAltered
	    cmDMX_FixSize		cmDMX_goto
	    cmDMX_Home			cmDMX_Left
	    cmDMX_Lock			cmDMX_LockData
	    cmDMX_NextRow		cmDMX_PgDn
	    cmDMX_PgUp			cmDMX_RecIndClicked
	    cmDMX_Reset			cmDMX_Right
	    cmDMX_RollCall		cmDMX_ScreenBottom
	    cmDMX_ScreenTop		cmDMX_ScrollBarChanged
	    cmDMX_SetupRecord		cmDMX_Top
	    cmDMX_Unlock		cmDMX_UnlockData
	    cmDMX_Up			cmDMX_WrongKey
	    cmDMX_XXXX			cmDMX_ZeroizeField
	    cmDMX_ZeroizeRecord

	    cmPRN_EndPage		cmPRN_FormFeed
	    cmPRN_LineFeed		cmPRN_NewPage
	    cmPRN_Reset			cmPRN_SetOptions


    FirstCmdNum	=  4400;

	Starting number for reserved commands.  tvDMX commands are all
	based on the cmDMX constant, which is based on this value.
	tvDMX reserves commands 4400 through 4999 for its own use, but
	you can change this by modifying this constant.
	(Unit RSET)


    FirstRegNum	=  4400;

	Starting number for object registration numbers.
	(Unit RSET)


    fldXXXX  =

	Field code notation for the supported data types:
	    fldSTR	=   'S';  --STRING field
	    fldSTRNUM	=   '#';  --numeric STRING field
	    fldCHAR	=   'C';  --CHARACTER field
	    fldCHARNUM	=   '0';  --numeric CHARACTER field
	    fldCHARVAL	=   'N';  --dBASE-formatted numeric CHARACTER field
	    fldBYTE	=   'B';  --BYTE field
	    fldSHORTINT	=   'J';  --SHORTINT field
	    fldWORD	=   'W';  --WORD field
	    fldINTEGER	=   'I';  --INTEGER field
	    fldLONGINT	=   'L';  --LONGINT field
	    fldREALNUM	=   'R';  --REAL number field  (uses type TREALNUM)
	    fldBOOLEAN	=   'X';  --BOOLEAN value field
	    fldHEXVALUE	=   'H';  --Hexadecimal numeric field
	    fldZEROMOD	=   'Z';  --zero template code modifier

	(Unit DMXGIZMA)


    fldDATE	=  ' WW-'^F^Z  + ^U+char(12) + ^P+char(2) +
		   #0'ZW-'^Z   + ^U+char(31) +
		   #0'ZZZW '^Z^F + ^P+char(-6) +
		   #0 + ^P+char(4);

	fldDATE defines what is called a "complex field".  The ^F control
	code ensures that these three integer fields receive the same field
	number.  ^Z will force zeroes to be displayed.  The ^P code uses the
	next character to adjust the data pointer forward 2 bytes, backward 6
	bytes, and then 4 bytes forward again.  This way, a sequence of three
	word fields of YEAR-MONTH-DAY can be displayed in MONTH-DAY-YEAR order,
	like this:  '  1-01-1992 '.
	The ^U code uses the next character as a maximum value for that field
	to limit months to 12 and days to 31.
	Refer to the section on control codes elsewhere in the documentation.
	(Unit DMXGIZMA)


    fldTIME	=  ' WW:'^F^Z + ^U+char(23) +
		   #0'ZW '^Z + ^U+char(59) +
		   #0'W'^F^H#0;  { seconds are hidden }

	fldTIME defines a complex field for HOURS:MINUTES (the SECONDS field
	is hidden).  The ^U code uses the next character as a maximum value
	for that field to limit hours to 23 and minutes to 59.
	fldDATE and fldTIME combine to display a DateTime type.
	(Unit DMXGIZMA)


    fldDATETIME  =  ' WW-'^F^Z + ^U+char(12) + ^P+char(2) +
		   #0'ZW-'^Z + ^U+char(31) +
		   #0'ZZZW '^Z^F + ^P+char(-6) +
		   '\' + ^P+char(4) +
		   ' WW:'^F^Z + ^U+char(23) +
		   #0'ZW:'^Z   + ^U+char(59) +
		   #0'ZW '^Z^F + ^U+char(59);  { seconds are not hidden }

	fldDATETIME is a modified concatenation of the fldDATE and fldTIME
	field templates --except that the seconds field is not hidden.
	See TMyApp.BusyWindow in program SAMPLES.PAS for examples using
	fldDATETIME and fldDATE and fldTIME.
	(Unit DMXGIZMA)


    kbCtrlA	 = $1E01;
    ...		    ...
    kbCtrlZ	 = $2C1A;
    kbShiftEnter = $1C0D;

	Additional keyboard codes not defined by Turbo Vision.
	(Unit RSET)


    Sunday	=   0;
    ...		   ...
    Saturday	=   6;

	Day-of-week constants.
	Example:  If (Day in [Sunday, Friday..Sunday]) then Exit;
	(Unit RSET)


    January	=   1;
    ...		   ...
    December	=  12;

	Month-number constants.
	Example:  If (DT.Month = April) and (DT.Day = 15) then Exit;
	(Unit RSET)


FUNCTIONS
---------

  proc  AssignWinRect (var Bounds : TRect;  MaxX, MaxY : integer);

	Assigns Bounds to fit into the desktop, with MaxX and MaxY as the
	maximum desired width and height.  Bounds is cut and moved to a
	cascaded position behind the currently active window.  (This is
	similar to what happens when a new file is loaded into the TP IDE.)
	New version takes advantage of TV 2's new GetTileRect() function.
	(Unit TVGIZMA)


  proc  DisposeSItems (AItems : PSItem);

	Dispose a chain of TSItems.
	(Unit DMXGIZMA)


  func  DmxStrLen (S : string)  : integer;

	Returns the length of the visible portions of a template string.
	(Unit DMXGIZMA)


  func  DParam (N : longint;  Next : pointer) : pointer;
  func  SParam (S : pstring;  Next : pointer) : pointer;

	Accessories that create a chain of parameter-pointers for the
	FormatStr() and MessageBox() procedures.  The Next parameter can
	be nested to create an array of pointers.  Examples:

	  FormatStr (S, '%s is at %d (%xH), and %d.',
		  SParam (@Name,
		  DParam (Num,
		  DParam (Num,
		  DParam (Num * RecordSize,
		  nil))))^   { requires a caret^ }
		);

	  MessageBox ('%s is at %d (%xH), and %d.',
		  SParam (@Name,
		  DParam (Num,
		  DParam (Num,
		  DParam (Num * RecordSize,
		  nil)))),   { no caret }
		mfInformation + mfOKButton
		);

	These functions are limited to 16 parameters.
	(Unit TVGIZMA)


  func  InitAppendFields (ATemplate : pstring) : DmxIDstr;

	Initializes a pointer to more field templates.  This can be used to
	increase the effective length of your template.

	Example:
	   Stx2 := 'WW,WWW |WW,WWW | CCCCCCCC ';
	   Stx1 := ' sssssssssssssss|WW,WWW |' + InitAppendFields (@Stx2);

	See also function InitTSItemFields() below.
	(Unit DMXGIZMA)


  func  InitBlobField (Len : integer; AccMode,Default : byte) : DmxIDstr;

	Initializes an unformatted data field of the given field length.
	BLOb fields take up space within the record but will not be displayed.
	You can use the GetBlob() --see previous page-- procedure to retrieve
	this data.  They are used for memo fields in MEMOSHOP.PAS.

	Example:
	   Stx := ' sssssssssssssss|WW,WWW |'
		+ InitBlobField (20, AccNormal, 0)
		+ 'WW,WWW |WW,WWW | CCCCCCCC ';
	(Unit DMXGIZMA)


  func  InitEnumField (ShowZ : boolean;
		       AccMode,Default : byte;
		       AItems : PSItem) : DmxIDstr;

	Initializes a tvDMX enumerated field list.

	Example:
	   Stx := ' sssssssssssssss|WW,WWW |'
		+  InitEnumField (FALSE, AccNormal, 0,
				NewSItem (' Zero ',
				NewSItem (' One',
				NewSItem (' Two',
				nil))))
		+ '| ###-#### |rrr,rrr.rrr ';
	(Unit DMXGIZMA)


  func  InitTSItemFields (ATemplates : PSItem) : DmxIDstr;

	Initializes a chain of TSItem templates.  This can be used to
	increase the effective length of your template.

	Example:
	   Stx := ' sssssssssssssss|WW,WWW |'
		+ InitTSItemFields (NewSItem (' sssssssssss`sssssssss|',
				    NewSItem ('($rrr,rrr.rr)|',
				    NewSItem (' CCCCC|WWW,WWW |',
				    nil))))
	(Unit DMXGIZMA)


  func  InsertText (Dialog :PDialog; Col,Row :integer; AText :string) : PView;

	Sizes, initializes, and inserts a single-line TStaticText view into
	the specified dialog window.  Example:

	  InsertText (Dialog, 4,3, 'Ready');

	It returns a PView pointer which is usually ignored.
	(Unit TVGIZMA)


  func  MaxItemStrLen (AItems : PSItem) : integer;

	Returns the maximum length of the strings in a TSItem chain.
	(Unit DMXGIZMA)


  func  NewVarItem (Name,Param : TMenuStr;   var Ind : pstring;
		KeyCode,Command,AHelpCtx : word;
		Next : PMenuItem) : PMenuItem;

	Creates a new menu item, and assigns a value to a status indicator.
	This is used by TAppA's NewSoundItem() and NewVideoItem() methods.
	(Unit TVGIZMA)


  func  ReadSItems (var S : TStream) : PSItem;

	Reads strings from a TSItem chain.
	(Unit DMXGIZMA)


  func  SItemsLen (S : PSItem) : integer;

	Returns the cumulative length of the strings in a TSItem chain.
	(Unit DMXGIZMA)


  func  SParam (S : pstring;  Next : pointer) : pointer;

	See function DParam()


  proc  TrimDialog (Window : PWindow);

	Shrinks and centers a dialog window to ease the design process.
	The dialog window should be initialized with the maximum size
	allowable.  TrimDialog() can be called after the controls are
	inserted to resize the window down to the maximum size needed.
	(Unit TVGIZMA)


  func  wnNextAvail : integer;

	Returns the next available (unused) window number.  This function
	was formerly called NextWindowNumber(), and it will still work
	under that name for a limited period of time.
	(Unit TVGIZMA)


  proc  WriteSItems (var S : TStream; Items : PSItem);

	Writes strings to a TSItem chain.
	(Unit DMXGIZMA)


OBJECTS
-------

    TAppA	=  OBJECT (TApplication)

	TApplication descendant that initializes TV's major components
	after saving the original user screen.  Its InitClock() virtual
	method initializes and inserts a TTimeView on the right side of
	the menu line.  The OutOfMemory() virtual method is overridden
	to provide a standard "Out of memory" message box.  The Idle()
	virtual method maintains the status of the cmCascade and cmTile
	commands, and then updates the TTimeView, if instantiated.
	Methods NewSoundItem() and NewVideoItem() should be used in your
	MenuBar initialization for special "indicator" menu items which
	will display the status of these options.  (See program SAMPLES.)
	NewVideoItem() will only add itself to the MenuBar on hi-res systems.
	The HandleEvent() method handles the cmDMX_WrongKey, cmUserScreen,
	cmToggleSound, cmToggleVideo, cmCascade and cmTile commands.
	(See the commands section --above-- for tvDMX commands.)
	The original user screen is re-displayed after termination.
	(Unit TVGIZMA)


    TLtdFrame	=  OBJECT (TFrame)

	Frame derivative designed to overwrite the Zoom icon when the
	window is at its maximum size.
	(Unit TVGIZMA)


    TLtdWindow	=  OBJECT (TWindow)

	Window that can be limited to a given maximum and/or minimum size.

	  constructor Init (var Bounds,ALimit : TRect;
			    ATitle : TTitleStr;
			    ANumber : integer);

	This is initialized with a second TRect parameter that defines its
	minimum size (in ALimit.A) and its maximum size (in ALimit.B).
	(Unit TVGIZMA)


    TTimeView	=  OBJECT (TView)

	Clock view that displays the time in AM/PM format.  This is
	initialized by the TAppA object.
	(Unit TVGIZMA)


    TUserScreen	=  OBJECT (TScroller)

	Scroller object that displays the original user screen that has
	been saved by the TAppA.Init() constructor.
	(Unit TVGIZMA)


